Overall: High aspirations are brought down by poor delivery in an otherwise great experience.  The good: There aren't many Jamaican places in the area, so right off that bad that's a great advantage. The yams and cabbage that came with my jerk chicken entree were fantastic. Our server was friendly and they have a good-sized menu, from both a food and drink perspective.  The not-so-good: The food here has great potential but is just missing a "wow" factor. Especially since the chicken itself, which is supposed to be the highlight, was underwhelming. I had to use a lot of sauce to soak up the dryness of it. Our server, while nice, was slow and forgetful, and our food took probably 30 minutes to arrive. And unfortunately, while I'm a fan of Jamaican atmosphere, the music was too loud.  Food/drink: 7/10 Atmosphere: 7/10 Service: 7/10
